news.title: Nagpur Smart City projects to be handed over to NMC by March 31
news.para: As there is no confirmation about an extension from the ministry of housing and urban affairs (MoHUA), the tenure of the special purpose vehicle (SPV) is set to end on March 31, 2025.

news.title: Cineline India sells hotel property in Goa for Rs 270 crore
news.para: Cineline India is planning to utilize the sale proceeds to fully repay its outstanding debt of Rz 108 crores related to the film exhibition business, achieving a debt-free status.

news.title: Civic bodies in Delhi extend property tax office hours to boost collections
news.para: NDMC set a target of collecting Rs 1,150 crore through service tax for the financial year 2024-2025 and has already surpassed Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: EPC model for Visakhapatnam, Vijayawada metro projects
news.para: If interim consultants were appointed instead, they would charge approximately 0.2% of the project cost — around Rs 20 crore — for a 12-month period, to assist with preliminary activities till general consultants are engaged.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues warrants to 426 property tax defaulters
news.para: NMC took the step after serving two notices over the last three months, asking 5000 defaulters to clear payments before March end. Officials said they want to recover as much property tax dues as possible by March 31.

news.title: Corporation to seek cut in property tax hike in Coimbatore
news.para: The meeting, held at Victoria Hall, was presided over by mayor K Ranganayaki, deputy mayor R Vetriselvan and corporation commissioner M Sivaguru Prabakaran.

news.title: Lucknow development body to survey vacant plots to curb fraud
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar on Friday directed officials to complete the process within 15 days. Furthermore, entry of suspicious individuals into the LDA office will be prohibited and a visitor pass will be mandatory for access to any desk.

news.title: Odisha government approves Jeypore master plan based on GIS & remote sensing
news.para: Initially published in July 2023, the plan underwent modifications based on consultations with stakeholders before receiving the final sanction.

news.title: Bombay HC rules developer cannot use insolvency law to avoid slum rehabilitation obligations
news.para: Builder’s appointment can be terminated despite a resolution plan (RP) in place under Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) proceedings, the HC said, except it cannot be done to recover “prior debts’’.

news.title: Mysuru civic body issues notices to property tax defaulters
news.para: MCC has 2.1 lakh properties in all its nine zones and 65 wards. Property tax and water cess are two major sources of revenue collection for MCC.

news.title: Accurate circle rates key to good governance: SC
news.para: Circle rates notified by govts determine the stamp duty to be paid by purchasers of land and properties in a locality, and helps the land acquisition officer quantify the fair compensation to be paid to landowners.

news.title: Maharashtra government issues draft notice on new rules for ‘iconic’ buildings
news.para: If the elevational, architectural, or special feature for a proposed iconic building is not utilised for habitable purposes, then a scrutiny committee headed by the municipal commissioner can allow these features free of floor space index.

news.title: Goa police to move tenant verification process online from next month
news.para: The new system is expected to streamline the procedure, making it more convenient for all parties involved. By moving the process online, the Goa Police hopes to enhance efficiency and reduce the time and effort required for tenant verification.

news.title: Odisha RERA empanels forensic audit firms to probe project ‘irregularities & delays’
news.para: The authority will deploy forensic audit teams in cases where projects show unusual delays, financial mismanagement or unauthorised pre-launch bookings.

news.title: Noida authority raises land allocation rates by 6% for housing & industry
news.para: Residential plots in A+ sectors—premium areas like sectors 14A, 15A and parts of 44—remain steady at Rs 1.75 lakh per sqm, for other areas plot prices now range from Rs 51,000 per sqm to Rs 1.3 lakh per sqm, with an increase of Rs 3,000 per sqm to Rs 7,500 per sqm.

news.title: EOW's probe not over case of fraud: Edelweiss Group
news.para: Edelweissin a statement said that ERPL had previously filed a commercial civil suit on the same matter, where the court denied any interim relief. Edelweiss said that its dispute with Ecstasy is a civil financial dispute, not a criminal offence.

news.title: Truhome Finance raises $100 million via ECB to fund affordable housing
news.para: ​The company has secured this funding through a social loan facility from DBS Bank and Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation (SMBC) as mandate lead Arranger and book-runner and joint social loan coordinators in this syndication, Truhome Finance said in a statement.

news.title: Vedanta Group submits expression of interest to acquire Jaiprakash Associates through insolvency
news.para: Sources said that Vedanta Group has submitted an Expression of Interest (EOI) to acquire the bankrupt JAL. Adani Group has also submitted an EOI.

news.title: Sebi issues framework for fast-track follow-on offer by REITs, InvITs
news.para: Additionally, the regulator has prescribed a lock-in provision of three years for the preferential issue of units of REITs (real estate investment trusts) and InVITs (infrastructure investment trusts) allotted to sponsors.

news.title: Zydus Family Trust buys Rs 200-crore apartment in Mumbai
news.para: The size of the flat is 17,384 sq ft and the per square foot rate is Rs 1.15 lakh. The apartment in Oberoi Realty's project 'Oberoi 360 West' was registered on March 27.
